feat: senior-friendly UX improvements and home button

- Increase base font size from 18px to 19px and boost sizes on all buttons,
  pills, search box, result items, and detail overlays for readability
- Improve text contrast: --text-light from #555 to #444, --text-muted from
  #aaa to #888 so low-emphasis text is still clearly legible
- Add persistent Home button (house icon) in top-left corner that resets all
  filters, closes overlays, and returns to the default week view
- Replace all tiny x close buttons with labeled "Close" buttons on every
  overlay (detail cards, timeline, plan, drives)
- Add full-width "Close" button at the bottom of detail cards so users don't
  have to scroll back up to dismiss
- Add confirmation dialog before hiding any item to prevent accidental removal
- Add Escape key support to close any open overlay
- Add visible focus rings (green outline) for keyboard navigation accessibility
- Add descriptive tooltips on all major buttons explaining what they do
- Show driving route on scenic drive map embeds instead of just a destination pin
- Remove leftover temp commit message file
